Conclusion
	Throughout this project, it has come to light that the garage parking automation is necessary to improve quality of life within communities that have this sort of issue. This project feasibility is fair, as the budget for the first prototype and research is valued at around $65. The implementation plan that is proposed in the schedule is on par with what we need to complete in each exact week and time. This project would be able to be implemented after the initial prototype is done to basically any parking garage that requires it. The overall need for this project and system is to improve the struggle that many people face when entering a parking garage and finding an open parking space. 



